cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category as it deals with speech enhancement and denoising. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves deep neural networks and optimization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a neural network. The use of perceptual speech metrics suggests it could also be classified under cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing). Finally, the end-to-end framework and optimization suggest it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
